// Oscillators — the smallest possible Akkado patch, plus a touch of
// vibrato to show how oscillators compose: an LFO modulates the
// frequency of a sine, and the result goes to both stereo channels.
//
// Replace `"sin"` with `"saw"`, `"tri"`, `"sqr"`, or `"noise"` to hear
// each waveform.

bpm = 120

vibrato = osc("sin", 5) * 3
osc("sin", 440 + vibrato) * 0.3 |> out(%, %)
